---
import SectionHeader from "./SectionHeader.astro";
---

<section
  id="origin"
  class="relative bg-paper px-6 pb-[140px] pt-[120px] text-paper-ink md:px-10"
>
  {
    /* Wider than max-w-site: the stretched display H2 needs the extra column
      width to clear the right-hand paragraphs (revision feedback #4). */
  }
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1360px]">
    <SectionHeader index="01" name="ORIGIN" meta="1997 → 2016" paper />
    {
      /* Left column gets the larger share and the H2 is capped a touch smaller so
        the stretched display face can't run under the right-hand column. */
    }
    <div
      class="grid grid-cols-1 items-start gap-[60px] md:grid-cols-[1.2fr_1fr]"
    >
      <h2 data-reveal class="h-display m-0 text-[clamp(26px,8.5vw,66px)]">
        Every architecture has a <span
          class="font-accent text-[1.06em] font-normal tracking-normal text-paper-accent-bright"
          >foundation</span
        ><span class="text-paper-accent-bright">.</span>
      </h2>
      <div>
        <p
          data-reveal
          class="mb-7 text-[19px] leading-[1.65] text-paper-ink/85"
        >
          1997. A nineteen-year-old petty officer serving in the U.S. Navy learns the first rule of
          mission-critical systems: <em class="font-accent text-[1.1em] not-italic"
            >they don't get to fail.</em>
        </p>
        <p
          data-reveal
          class="mb-7 text-[19px] leading-[1.65] text-paper-ink/85"
        >
          Four years in the Navy. Then decades architecting enterprise systems
        for the Army, the Navy, Bank of America, Capital One, a State agency, and a startup. The scale kept growing. The challenges never stopped.
          But the rule never changed.
        </p>
        <div
          data-reveal
          class="flex flex-wrap gap-8 border-t border-paper-line pt-5 font-mono text-[12px] tracking-[0.1em] text-paper-ink/55"
        >
          <span>US NAVY · 1997</span>
          <span>US ARMY · 2002</span>
          <span>BANK OF AMERICA · 2008</span>
          <span>Capital One · 2016</span>
          <span>VDOT · 2024</span>
          <span>1800Unlocks · 2026</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
